pr_nif_0000_21981_1.study_title: Double-Blind, Placebo-Controlled Assessment Of Potential Interactions Between Intravenous Methamphetamine And Osmotic-Release Methylphenidate (Oros-Mph)
pr_nif_0000_21981_1.study_description: The primary objective of this study is to determine the safety of the OROS-MPH concurrent with i.v. d-methamphetamine infusions of 15 mg and 30 mg. Safety outcome measures include cardiovascular responses [heart rate (HR), blood pressure (BP), and electrocardiograph (ECG) measurements], oral temperature, adverse events (AEs), and clinical laboratory analyses.
pr_nif_0000_21981_1.keywords: Phase 1B, Oral Osmotic-release, Methylphenidate, Methamphetamine, Intravenous, Stimulant
